tlawed%20Indigenous%20burning%20practices%20and%20started%20suppressing%20wildfires%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20massive%20buildup%20of%20flammable%20brush%20and%20trees.%20That%20combined%20with%20the%20dry%2C%20hot%20conditions%20caused%20by%20the%20climate%20crisis%20has%20left%20much%20of%20the%20country%20at%20a%20dangerously%20high%20risk%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpano-ai-5g-wildfire-detection-tool-contains-fires-faster-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edevastating%20wildfires%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20top%2010%20most%20destructive%20years%20by%20acreage%20burned%20have%20all%20occurred%20since%202004.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20late%201960s%20and%20early%201970s%2C%20federal%20land%20managers%20reevaluated%20their%20approach%20to%20fire%20and%20did%20the%20first%20prescribed%20burns%20in%20national%20parks.%20We're%20still%20making%20up%20for%20lost%20time%3A%20Scientists%20and%20land%20managers%20say%20millions%20more%20acres%20of%20prescribed%20burns%20are%20necessary%20to%20keep%20the%20country%20from%20burning%20out%20of%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20task%20doesn't%20match%20that%20of%20the%20labor%20force%2C%20whose%20focus%20is%20often%20extinguishing%20fires%2C%20not%20starting%20them.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffema-helene-milton-relief-funding-congress-disaster-victims-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EResponding%20to%20the%20increase%20in%20natural%20disasters%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20left%20America%20with%20few%20resources%20to%20actually%20keep%20them%20from%20happening.%20As%20Mark%20Charlton%2C%20a%20prescribed-fire%20specialist%20with%20The%20Nature%20Conservancy%2C%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20need%20more%20people%2C%20and%20we%20need%20more%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20fall%2C%20I%20outfitted%20myself%20in%20fire-resistant%20clothing%20and%20boots%2C%20donned%20a%20hard%20hat%2C%20and%20joined%20a%20training%20program%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffirenetworks.org%2Ftrex%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETREX%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20better%20understand%20how%20prescribed%20burns%20work.%20TREX%20hosts%20collaborative%20burns%20to%20provide%20training%20opportunities%20in%20the%20field%20for%20people%20from%20different%20employers%20and%20backgrounds.%20The%20hope%20is%20that%20more%20people%20will%20earn%20the%20qualifications%20they%20need%20to%20lead%20and%20participate%20in%20burns%20for%20the%20agencies%20they%20work%20for%20back%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225184%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Firemen%20training%20in%20a%20hill%20side.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67508420ef9a5d904789dd4f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223888%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOur%20team%20would%20walk%20across%20the%20area%20we%20planned%20to%20burn%20to%20collect%20data%20on%20weather%20and%20fire%20behavior.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kara%20Karboski%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20program's%20emphasis%20on%20learning%2C%20coupled%20with%20the%20support%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Idaho's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theconfluencelab.org%2Fartists-in-fire-residency%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArtists-in-Fire%20Residency%3C%2Fa%3E%20(which%20helped%20pay%20my%20way)%2C%20is%20why%20I%2C%20a%20journalist%20with%20no%20fire%20jobs%20on%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%20could%20join%20a%20prescribed-fire%20module%20of%20about%20two%20dozen%20more%20experienced%20participants.%20I%20had%20to%20pass%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outsideonline.com%2Foutdoor-adventure%2Fexploration-survival%2Fwildland-firefighter-pack-test-fitness%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efitness%20test%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20speed%20walking%20three%20miles%20with%20a%2045-pound%20backpack%20in%20under%2045%20minutes%20%E2%80%94%20take%2040%20hours'%20worth%20of%20online%20coursework%2C%20and%20complete%20field-operations%20training%20to%20participate%20as%20a%20crew%20member.%20While%20hundreds%20of%20people%20have%20participated%20in%20TREX%20burns%20across%20the%20country%20since%20the%20program's%20inception%20in%202008%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-climate-change-national-parks%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edramatic%20growth%20of%20wildfires%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20outpacing%20the%20number%20of%20people%20being%20trained%20to%20reduce%20their%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Forest%20Service%20manages%20193%20million%20acres%20of%20forests%20and%20grasslands%20across%20the%20country%2C%20burning%20an%20average%20of%20about%201.4%20million%20acres%2C%20roughly%20the%20size%20of%20Delaware%2C%20each%20year%20with%20prescribed%20burns.%20It%20burned%20a%20record%202%20million%20acres%20in%20fiscal%202023.%20But%20it's%20still%20not%20enough%20preparation%2C%20considering%20wildfires%20have%20burned%20over%2010%20million%20acres%20in%20recent%20years%20and%20people%20continue%20building%20and%20living%20in%20wildfire-prone%20areas.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20huge%20workload%20we%20have%2C%20and%20we%20know%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Adam%20Mendonca%2C%20a%20deputy%20director%20of%20fire%20and%20aviation%20management%20for%20the%20Forest%20Service%20who%20oversees%20the%20agency's%20prescribed-fire%20program.%20The%20agency%20plans%20to%20chip%20away%20at%20the%20problem%20with%20the%20roughly%2011%2C300%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwildland-firefighter-what-job-involves-more-preventing-not-fighting-fire-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewildland%20firefighters%20it%20employs%3C%2Fa%3E%20each%20year%20who%20squeeze%20the%20work%20in%20during%20the%20offseason%2C%20when%20there%20are%20fewer%20fires%20to%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20relying%20on%20wildland%20firefighters%20can%20be%20problematic.%20%26quot%3BWe%20only%20have%20those%20resources%20for%20a%20short%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Charlton%2C%20who%20served%20as%20the%20incident%20commander%20on%20the%20Washington%20burns%20I%20joined%20this%20fall.%20%26quot%3BAfter%20a%20long%20fire%20season%2C%20people%20are%20exhausted.%20It's%20hard%20to%20get%20people%20to%20commit.%26quot%3B%20Plus%2C%20wildfires%20are%20increasingly%20overlapping%20with%20the%20ideal%20windows%20to%20do%20prescribed%20burns%20%E2%80%94%20often%20the%20spring%20and%20the%20fall%2C%20when%20conditions%20are%20cooler%20and%20wetter%2C%20making%20fires%20easier%20to%20tame.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20especially%20true%20this%20year%3A%20Multiple%20large%20fires%20burned%20across%20the%20West%20into%20October.%20These%20late-season%20wildfires%2C%20coupled%20with%20two%20hurricanes%20that%20firefighters%20helped%20respond%20to%2C%20strained%20federal%20resources.%20That%20month%2C%20the%20nation's%20fire-preparedness%20level%20increased%20to%20a%205%20%E2%80%94%20the%20highest%20level%20%E2%80%94%20indicating%20the%20country's%20emergency%20crews%20were%20at%20their%20maximum%20capacity%20and%20would've%20struggled%20to%20respond%20to%20new%20incidents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20the%20elevated%20preparedness%20level%2C%20the%20National%20Multi-Agency%20Coordinating%20Group%20urged%20%26quot%3Bextreme%20caution%26quot%3B%20in%20executing%20new%20prescribed%20fires%2C%20saying%20backup%20firefighters%20or%20equipment%20might%20not%20be%20available.%20%26quot%3BWe%20get%20to%20the%20point%20where%20we're%20competing%20for%20resources%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kyle%20Lapham%2C%20the%20certified-burner-program%20manager%20for%20the%20Washington%20State%20Department%20of%20Natural%20Resources%20and%20the%20burn%20boss%20on%20the%20Washington%20burns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20qualification%20shortage.%20Prescribed%20burns%20require%20a%20well-rounded%20group%20with%20a%20variety%20of%20expertise%20and%20positions%20%E2%80%94%20including%20a%20burn%20boss%2C%20who%20runs%20the%20show%20and%20must%20have%20years%20of%20training.%20Charlton%20estimated%20that%20hundreds%20more%20qualified%20burn%20bosses%20are%20necessary%20to%20tackle%20nationwide%20prescribed-burn%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Firemen%20trainee%20making%20a%20plan%20behind%20a%20pickup%20truck.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675084fe7929f317fb4fec0b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20lot%20of%20planning%20%E2%80%94%20and%20trained%20expertise%20%E2%80%94%20is%20required%20before%20any%20burning%20can%20begin.%20%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Adam%20Gebauer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20concerning%20is%20an%20interest%20shortage.%20The%20Forest%20Service%20has%20struggled%20to%20hire%20for%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fnews%2Fus-news%2Fground-zero-attrition-california-federal-fire-crews-understaffed-fire-threat-n1267882%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emaintain%20its%20federal%20firefighting%20force%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20in%20large%20part%20because%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffirefighters-paid-less-than-3-an-hour-by-federal-contractor-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epoor%20pay%20%3C%2Fa%3E(federal%20firefighter%20base%20pay%20was%20raised%20to%20%2415%20an%20hour%20in%202022)%20and%20other%20labor%20disputes%20over%20job%20classifications%2C%20pay%20raises%2C%20staffing%2C%20and%20more.%20The%20agency%20is%20also%20expecting%20budget%20cuts%20next%20year%20and%20has%20already%20said%20it%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20hire%20its%20usual%20seasonal%20workforce%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegislation%20inching%20its%20way%20through%20Congress%20could%20help%2C%20though%20its%20fate%20under%20a%20new%20administration%20is%20unclear.%20The%20National%20Prescribed%20Fire%20Act%20of%202024%20would%20direct%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20to%20the%20Forest%20Service%20and%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20the%20Interior%20for%20prescribed%20burns%2C%20including%20investment%20in%20training%20a%20skilled%20workforce%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20hasn't%20progressed%20past%20a%20Senate%20subcommittee%20hearing%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20a%20boost%20in%20funding%2C%20the%20agency%20will%20continue%20relying%20heavily%20on%20partnerships%20with%20nonprofits%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnature-photography-wildlife-photos-contest-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Nature%20Conservancy%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20National%20Forest%20Foundation%20to%20staff%20prescribed%20burns.%20The%20Forest%20Service%20also%20recently%20expanded%20its%20Prescribed%20Fire%20Training%20Center%20to%20host%20educational%20opportunities%20out%20West.%20Critically%2C%20though%2C%20time%20is%20of%20the%20essence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20TREX%20training%20in%20October%2C%20about%2020%20foresters%20and%20firefighters%20from%20as%20far%20south%20as%20Texas%20and%20as%20far%20north%20as%20British%20Columbia%20worked%20beside%20me.%20Our%20group%20included%20employees%20of%20the%20Washington%20Department%20of%20Natural%20Resources%20and%20two%20citizens%20of%20the%20nearby%20Spokane%20Tribe%20of%20Indians%2C%20who%20have%20a%20robust%20prescribed-fire%20program%20of%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20two%20weeks%20I%20got%20a%20front-row%20seat%20to%20how%20much%20planning%20(sometimes%20years)%20and%20time%20a%20single%20prescribed%20burn%20takes.%20We%20conducted%20several%20burns%20in%20the%20mountains%20north%20of%20Spokane%20on%20the%20property%20of%20a%20receptive%20landowner%20who'd%20hosted%20TREX%20in%20previous%20years.%20He%20provided%20the%20training%20ground%20and%2C%20in%20exchange%2C%20got%20work%20done%20on%20his%20property.%20This%20isn't%20a%20common%20scenario%20%E2%80%94%20burning%20on%20private%20land%20can%20be%20more%20complicated%2C%20and%20so%20more%20burns%20happen%20on%20state%20or%20federal%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20arrived%2C%20the%20burn's%20incident-management%20team%20had%20already%20put%20together%20a%20burn%20plan%20detailing%20our%20objectives%20%E2%80%94%20reducing%20wildfire%20risk%20to%20the%20landowner's%20house%2C%20thinning%20small%20tree%20saplings%2C%20knocking%20down%20invasive%20weeds%2C%20opening%20up%20more%20wildlife%20habitat%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20exact%20weather%20conditions%2C%20like%20wind%20speed%2C%20relative%20humidity%2C%20and%20temperature%2C%20we%20needed%20to%20safely%20burn.%20Prescribed%20burns%20on%20federal%20lands%20also%20go%20through%20an%20environmental%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20site%2C%20we%20scouted%20contained%20areas%20we%20would%20burn%2C%20called%20units%2C%20with%20trainees%20making%20additional%20plans%20for%20how%20to%20ignite%20and%20control%20fires.%20Keeping%20a%20fire%20in%20its%20intended%20location%2C%20called%20%26quot%3Bholding%2C%26quot%3B%20meant%20lots%20of%20prep%20work%2C%20like%20digging%20shallow%20trenches%20to%20box%20the%20fire%20in.%20During%20the%20burn%2C%20teams%20monitored%20smoke%20and%20occasionally%20sprayed%20the%20larger%20trees%20we%20wanted%20to%20preserve%20with%20water%20when%20flames%20threatened%20their%20canopies%3B%20others%20poured%20fuel%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20igniting%20bushes%2C%20grass%2C%20and%20smaller%20trees%20to%20slowly%20build%20the%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224758%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fireman%20trainee%20digging%20trenches%20during%20training%20for%20wildfires.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675083bfef9a5d904789dcf8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223569%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThose%20nights%2C%20I%20went%20to%20bed%20dreaming%20of%20smoke.%20I%20left%20with%20a%20deeper%20appreciation%20for%20those%20who%20set%20fires%20for%20a%20living.%20%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kara%20Karboski%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EManaging%20the%20fire%20didn't%20end%20when%20we%20finished%20burning%20the%2030%20or%20so%20acres.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20it%20can%20involve%20days%20of%20monitoring%20and%20cleanup.%20To%20make%20sure%20the%20fire%20was%20out%2C%20my%20crew%20and%20I%20combed%20through%20areas%20we'd%20burned%20the%20day%20before%20for%20smoke%20or%20heat.%20If%20we%20discovered%20something%20still%20smoking%2C%20we'd%20churn%20up%20the%20ground%20with%20a%20shovel%20or%20pickax%2C%20douse%20the%20hot%20spot%20with%20water%2C%20and%20repeat.%20Just%20when%20we%20thought%20we%20were%20done%2C%20we'd%20find%20another%20spot%20we'd%20missed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20to%20bed%20those%20nights%20dreaming%20of%20little%20puffs%20of%20smoke%20and%20woke%20up%20with%20small%20flakes%20of%20ash%20embedded%20behind%20my%20ears.%20The%20work%20was%20rewarding%20and%20exhausting%20%E2%80%94%20I%20left%20with%20a%20deeper%20appreciation%20for%20the%20workers%20who%20do%20it%20for%20a%20living.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20every%20prescribed%20burn%20is%20different%2C%20it's%20always%20a%20careful%20equation.%20Everything%20needs%20to%20line%20up%3A%20supportive%20communities%2C%20the%20right%20weather%2C%20and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20workers%20necessary%20to%20plan%2C%20burn%2C%20and%20extinguish.%20Only%20then%20can%20you%20light%20the%20match.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fkylie-mohr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EKylie%20Mohr%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20Montana-based%20freelance%20journalist%20and%20correspondent%20for%20the%20magazine%20High%20Country%20News.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-wildfire-crisis-labor-shortage-prescribed-fires-climate-change-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734602521000