ort%20to%20hobble%20the%20world's%20second-largest%20economy.%20Parsons%20has%20asked%20himself%20if%20Trump%20would%20ban%20travel%20from%20China%20to%20further%20these%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETrump%20could%20decrease%20access%20to%20a%20commonly%20used%20visa%20type%20by%20tech%20companies%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223404%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Google%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d38789a3bd891424f865b0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222553%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGoogle%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%20first%20entered%20the%20country%20on%20the%20same%20visa%20type%20that%20President-elect%20Donald%20Trump%20suspended%20during%20his%20first%20term.%3Cp%3EChristoph%20Soeder%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tech%20sector%20is%20the%20biggest%20beneficiary%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-startups-sponsor-h1b-work-visas-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EH-1B%20visa%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20allows%20employers%20to%20fill%20specialty%20roles%20with%20highly%20educated%20foreign%20workers.%20Last%20year%2C%20more%20than%20half%20of%20these%20visas%20went%20to%20workers%20in%20computer-related%20roles%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20US%20Citizenship%20and%20Immigration%20Services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20Trump's%20first%20term%2C%20government%20data%20shows%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmore-h-1b-visa-applications-rejected-under-trump-2019-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edenial%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20new%20employees%20and%20requests%20for%20further%20evidence%20of%20eligibility%20surged.%20In%202020%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration%20temporarily%20paused%20the%20issuance%20of%20new%20green%20cards%20and%20many%20work%20visa%20types%2C%20arguing%20that%20this%20would%20protect%20American%20jobs%20during%20a%20pandemic%20decline%20in%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20has%20moved%20to%20reverse%20some%20of%20these%20policies%20and%20facilitate%20the%20processing%20of%20work-related%20visas.%20In%20December%2C%20the%20White%20House%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dhs.gov%2Fnews%2F2024%2F12%2F17%2Fdhs-strengthens-h-1b-program-allowing-us-employers-more-quickly-fill-critical-jobs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20new%20regulations%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20allow%20the%20immigration%20agency%20to%20process%20applications%20more%20quickly%20for%20most%20individuals%20who%20had%20previously%20been%20approved%20for%20an%20H-1B%20visa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJason%20Finkelman%20said%20the%20new%20rules%20%26quot%3Bgive%20predictability%20to%20employers%20and%20foreign%20nationals%20on%20the%20extensions%20of%20their%20visa%20petitions%20when%20there%20has%20been%20no%20change%20in%20the%20job%20duties%20or%20the%20employer.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%20that%20it's%20plausible%20Trump%20can%20withdraw%20the%20regulations%20once%20he%20takes%20office%2C%20however.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElizabeth%20Goss%20offered%20a%20more%20optimistic%20outlook.%20She%20suggested%20that%20if%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-elon-musk-disagrees-with-trump-visa-suspension-2020-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20Trump's%20ear%2C%20he%20might%20be%20able%20to%20persuade%20the%20president%20to%20leave%20the%20program%20untouched%20or%20even%20expand%20the%20number%20of%20visas%20issued%2C%20though%20such%20a%20move%20hasn't%20been%20made%20since%20President%20Bill%20Clinton%20raised%20the%20limit%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20dot-com%20bubble.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECanadians%20could%20be%20turned%20away%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223696%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Justin%20Trudeau%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675b7e4552dd0818d1a6def6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%