sk-friendship-7284153%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22During%20her%20address%20in%20a%20parliamentary%20session%20ahead%20of%20this%20week's%20European%20Union%20summit%20in%20Brussels%2C%20Georgia%20Meloni%20insisted%20that%20he%20has%20independence%20and%20will%20not%20be%20influenced%20by%20Elon%20Musk's%20business%20interests.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdont-take-orders-from-anyone-giorgia-meloni-defends-elon-musk-friendship-7284153%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Laapataa%20Oscar%3A%20Why%20Does%20India%20Get%20The%20Oscars%20So%20Wrong%20Every%20Year%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWe%20may%20all%20have%20been%20hoping%20against%20hope%20for%20happier%20tidings%2C%20but%20it%20was%20no%20surprise%20at%20all%20that%20%3Cem%3ELaapataa%20Ladies%3C%2Fem%3E%20fell%20short%20of%20the%20shortlist%20of%2015%20titles%20that%20will%20be%20considered%20for%20nomination%20in%20the%20International%20Best%20Feature%20Film%20category%20at%20the%2097th%20Academy%20Awards.%20The%20elimination%20is%2C%20however%2C%20no%20reflection%20on%20the%20intrinsic%20merits%20of%20the%20Kiran%20Rao%20film.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELaapataa%20Ladies%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ehad%20much%20going%20for%20it%2C%20but%20it%20simply%20wasn't%20in%20the%20right%20place%20at%20the%20right%20time.%20It%20lost%20its%20way%20because%20it%20was%20up%20against%20a%20bunch%20of%20international%20festival%20circuit%20favourites%20that%20had%20a%20headstart%20from%20the%20moment%20they%20were%20named%20as%20contenders%20by%20their%20respective%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EI'm%20Still%20Here%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20Brazilian%20entry%2C%20won%20the%20best%20screenplay%20prize%20in%20Venice.%20Ireland's%20hip-hop%20musical%20%3Cem%3EKneecap%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20the%20Czech%20historical%20drama%20%3Cem%3EWaves%3C%2Fem%3E%20were%20audience%20award%20winners%20at%20Sundance%20and%20Karlovy%20Vary%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20not%20even%20talking%20here%20about%20Jacques%20Audiard's%20%3Cem%3EEmilia%20Perez%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20Mohammad%20Rasoulof's%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Seed%20of%20the%20Sacred%20Fig%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20Farsi-language%20film%20that%20is%20Germany's%20official%20entry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBarring%3Cem%3E%20Emilia%20Perez%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20French%20production%20set%20in%20Mexico%20and%20filmed%20in%20Spanish%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Seed%20of%20the%20Sacred%20Fig%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20none%20of%20the%20aforementioned%20films%20were%20preceded%20by%20the%20sort%20of%20global%20buzz%20that%20Payal%20Kapadia's%20%3Cem%3EAll%20We%20Imagine%20as%20Light%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewas.%20But%20the%20all-male%2C%20fossilised%20Film%20Federation%20of%20India%20(FFI)%20jury%20ignored%20the%20Cannes%20Grand%20Prix%20winner%20on%20the%20risible%20ground%20that%20it%20wasn't%20%26quot%3BIndian%20enough%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20gilt-edged%20opportunity%20lost%20and%20not%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20Contrast%20the%20%3Cem%3EAWIAL%3C%2Fem%3E%20snub%20by%20FFI%20with%20the%20arc%20of%20British-Indian%20filmmaker%20Sandhya%20Suri's%20social%20commentary-laden%2C%20Hindi-language%20police%20procedural%3Cem%3E%20Santosh%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20UK's%20official%20Oscar%20entry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESantosh%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewas%20found%20British%20enough%20to%20be%20granted%20the%20honour%20of%20being%20a%20rare%20UK%20contender%20in%20the%20non-English%20language%20film%20category%20at%20the%20Oscars.%20That%20the%20India-set%20drama%20starring%20Shahana%20Goswami%20and%20Sunita%20Rajwar%20is%20in%20the%20Oscar%20shortlist%20is%20proof%20that%20cinema%20is%20a%20language%20unto%20itself%20that%20transcends%20barriers%20of%20language%2C%20culture%20and%20milieu.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20selection%20process%20to%20pick%20India's%20entry%20for%20the%20Best%20International%20Feature%20Film%20Oscar%20has%20been%20the%20butt%20of%20ridicule%20for%20years.%20Justifiably%20so.%20The%20wise%20men%20(and%20occasionally%20women)%20who%20deliberate%20upon%20which%20film%20will%20represent%20the%20world's%20largest%20movie%20producing%20nation%20at%20the%20Oscars%20always%20find%20ways%20of%20getting%20it%20horribly%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20outdid%20themselves%20in%202013%2C%20the%20year%20they%20bafflingly%20plumbed%20for%20Gyan%20Correa's%20Gujarati%20film%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EGood%20Road%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0at%20the%20expense%20of%20Ritesh%20Batra's%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Lunchbox%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20Irrfan-Nimrat%20Kaur-Nawazuddin%20Siddiqui%20starrer%20that%20began%20its%20journey%20in%20Cannes%20and%20travelled%20the%20world%20thereafter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202012%2C%20too%2C%20FFI%20tied%20itself%20up%20in%20knots.%20It%20picked%20Anurag%20Basu's%20%3Cem%3EBarfi!%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20India's%20official%20Oscar%20entry.%20The%20film%2C%20expectedly%2C%20had%20no%20chance%20of%20ever%20being%20in%20the%20reckoning%20in%20a%20year%20in%20which%20Asghar%20Farhadi's%20piercing%20marital%20discord%20drama%3Cem%3E%20A%20Separation%3C%2Fem%3E%20took%20home%20the%20Oscar.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20SS%20Rajamouli's%20action%20extravaganza%3Cem%3E%20RRR%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20all%20the%20rage%20globally%20and%20was%20tipped%20to%20be%20a%20strong%20contender%20for%20the%20Best%20International%20Feature%20Film%20Oscar.%20FFI%20chose%20the%20Gujarati%20coming-of-age%20film%20by%20Pan%20Nalin%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EChello%20Show%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20instead.%20Many%20of%20those%20who%20championed%20%3Cem%3ERRR%3C%2Fem%3E's%20cause%20felt%20that%20the%20selection%20was%20inexplicable%20and%20it%20stymied%20any%20chance%20India%20had%20of%20a%20fair%20shot%20at%20an%20Oscar.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20all%20these%20years%2C%20India%20has%20managed%20to%20snag%20only%20three%20nominations%20in%20the%20Best%20International%20Feature%20Film%20Oscar%20category%20-%20in%201957%20(%3Cem%3EMother%20India%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%201988%20(%3Cem%3ESalaam%20Bombay!%3C%2Fem%3E)%20and%202001%20(%3Cem%3ELagaan)%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%3Cem%3EMother%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20reportedly%20lost%20by%20a%20whisker%20-%20one%20vote%20-%20to%20Federico%20Fellini's%3Cem%3E%20Nights%20of%20Cabiria.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20also%20suggested%20without%20any%20official%20corroboration%20that%20%3Cem%3ELagaan%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20too%2C%20ran%20the%20eventual%20Oscar%20winner%20of%202001%2C%20Danis%20Tanovic's%20%3Cem%3ENo%20Man's%20Land%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Etantalisingly%20close.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMira%20Nair's%20%3Cem%3ESalaam%20Bombay!%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20winner%20of%20the%20Camera%20d'Or%20in%20Cannes%20in%201988%2C%20ranks%20among%20the%20better%20choices%20that%20India%20has%20made.%20The%20film%20lost%20to%20Bille%20August's%20%3Cem%3EPelle%20the%20Conqueror%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20a%20year%20that%20also%20had%20Istvan%20Szabo's%20%3Cem%3EHanussen%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20Pedro%20Almodovar's%20%3Cem%3EWomen%20on%20the%20Verge%20of%20a%20Nervous%20Breakdown%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20the%20running.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%20the%201970s%2C%20India's%20Oscar%20entry%20selectors%20seemed%20to%20be%20aware%20of%20what%20they%20were%20doing.%20The%20films%20that%20they%20chose%20included%20Satyajit%20Ray's%20%3Cem%3EApur%20Sansar%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1959)%2C%20%3Cem%3EMahanagar%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1963)%20and%20%3Cem%3EShatranj%20Ke%20Khiladi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1978)%2C%20MS%20Sathyu's%20%3Cem%3EGarm%20Hawa%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1974)%20and%20Shyam%20Benegal's%20%3Cem%3EManthan%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1977).%20None%20of%20them%20went%20the%20distance%20but%20they%20were%20not%20embarrassments%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20selection%20process%20plummeted%20precipitously%20and%20assumed%20farcical%20proportions%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20hitting%20its%20nadir%20in%201998.%20That%20year%20India%20sent%20the%20S%20Shankar%20potboiler%20%3Cem%3EJeans%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20the%20Academy%20Awards%20because%20Ashok%20Amritraj%20was%20the%20film's%20lead%20producer.%20The%20calculation%20of%20the%20jury%20was%20that%20because%20Amritraj%20was%20based%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20enjoyed%20considerable%20clout%20in%20Hollywood%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EJeans%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewould%20stand%20a%20chance%20of%20muscling%20its%20way%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20forgot%20that%20no%20matter%20how%20much%20trash%20is%20pushed%2C%20it%20can%20never%20turn%20into%20gold%20dust.%20%3Cem%3EJeans%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20S%20Shankar's%20second%20film%20in%20three%20years%20-%20the%20first%20was%20the%20Kamal%20Haasan%20vehicle%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1996)%20-%20to%20be%20chosen%20as%20India's%20official%20Oscar%20entry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20excitement%20that%20the%20Oscar%20nomination%20for%20%3Cem%3ELagaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20generated%2C%20it%20was%20felt%20in%20certain%20quarters%20that%20the%20time%20had%20finally%20come%20for%20India%20to%20up%20the%20ante%20and%20look%20for%20greater%20glory%20at%20the%20Academy%20Awards.%20But%20the%20foot%20in%20the%20door%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20flash%20in%20the%20pan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202002%2C%20the%20year%20after%20%3Cem%3ELagaan's%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ememorable%20run%20at%20the%20Academy%20Awards%2C%20the%20FFI%2C%20in%20its%20wisdom%2C%20nominated%20Sanjay%20Leela%20Bhansali's%3Cem%3E%20Devdas%3C%2Fem%3E%20instead%20of%20Mani%20Ratnam's%20%3Cem%3EKannathil%20Muthamittal%3C%2Fem%3E%20(%3Cem%3EA%20Peck%20on%20the%20Cheek%3C%2Fem%3E)%20or%20Buddhadeb%20Dasgupta's%20%3Cem%3EMondo%20Meyer%20Upakhyan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(%3Cem%3EA%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%3Cem%3ETale%20of%20a%20Naughty%20Girl%3C%2Fem%3E).%20Not%20that%20either%20of%20snubbed%20films%20would%20have%20earned%20a%20nomination%2C%20let%20alone%20win%2C%20but%20they%20had%20far%20greater%20cinematic%20potential.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPretty%20much%20the%20same%20story%20was%20repeated%20in%202007.%20India's%20official%20Oscar%20entry%20that%20year%20was%20Vidhu%20Vinod%20Chopra's%20Amitabh%20Bachchan-led%20multi-starrer%20%3Cem%3EEklavya%20%3C%2Fem%3E-%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Royal%20Guard.%20%3C%2Fem%3EAmong%20the%20titles%20that%20FFI%20could%20have%20chosen%20ahead%20of%20%3Cem%3EEklavya%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20Deepa%20Mehta's%20%3Cem%3EWater%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20third%20film%20of%20her%20Elements%20trilogy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20fair%2C%20there%20have%20been%20years%20when%20FFI%20backed%20the%20most%20deserving%20horse%20and%20raised%20hopes%20of%20a%20breakthrough.%20In%201994%2C%20Shekhar%20Kapur's%20international%20breakout%3Cem%3E%20Bandit%20Queen%3C%2Fem%3E%20earned%20the%20nod.%20In%202015%2C%20it%20was%20the%20turn%20of%20Chaitanya%20Tamhane's%20critically%20acclaimed%20festival%20hit%20%3Cem%3ECourt%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20very%20next%20year%2C%20India%20sent%20Vetrimaaran's%20gritty%20%3Cem%3EVisaranai%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20the%20Oscars.%20In%202017%2C%20FFI%20got%20it%20right%20once%20again%2C%20choosing%20Amit%20V%20Masurkar's%20%3Cem%3ENewton%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20had%20premiered%20early%20in%20the%20year%20in%20the%20Forum%20section%20of%20the%20Berlin%20Film%20Festival.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20another%20Tamil%20film%2C%20debutant%20PS%C2%A0Vinothraj's%3Cem%3E%20Koozhangal%3C%2Fem%3E%20(%3Cem%3EPebbles%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20winner%20of%20the%20Tiger%20Award%20at%20the%20International%20Film%20Festival%20Rotterdam%2C%20made%20the%20cut.%20But%20small%20films%20with%20limited%20resources%20often%20lack%20the%20means%20to%20lobby%20hard%20enough%20to%20attract%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20Academy%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20admittedly%20isn't%20a%20level%20playing%20field%2C%20but%20had%20the%20FFI%20had%20a%20better%20idea%20of%20how%20to%20go%20about%20things%2C%20India's%20wait%20for%20a%20Best%20International%20Feature%20Film%20Oscar%20might%20have%20ended%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734595200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Foi7job7g_laapataa_625x300_19_December_24.jpg%22%2C%2